<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="guess-v">guess <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɡes/    美 /ɡes/  </p>
<p>vi &amp; vt</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>猜；推测；猜中：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Can you guess this riddle?
你能猜出这个谜语吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Not knowing which way to go, I had to guess.
不知道该走哪条路，我只好猜一猜。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>guess … to be:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I guess his age to be around 30.
我猜他大概30岁左右。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>guess + (that) / wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Guess what I'll be doing this summer?
猜猜今年暑假我要做什么？</p><footer>2016 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>想；认为：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>I guess</strong> what you were really trying to say is that you've got nothing to do these days.
我想你真正要表达的是你这几天无所事事。</p><footer>2009 湖北书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Are you ready to go?
你准备好出发了吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— <strong>I guess so / not</strong>.
我想是的/没有。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Jack, you seem excited.
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_? I won the first prize in the English speech contest.  （2015 天津）<br />
A.Guess what<br />
B.So what<br />
C.Pardon me<br />
D.Who cares  </li>
<li>— The boys are not doing a good job at all, are they?
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ .<br />
A.I guess not so<br />
B.I don’t guess<br />
C.I don’t guess so<br />
D.I guess not  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. A  2. D  </p></div>